### Identity Service - Health Check
GET http://localhost:5001/api/auth/health

### 1. Create/Register a new user
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Test123!",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

### 2. Login
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Test123!"
}

### 3. Refresh Token (replace with actual refresh token from login)
GET http://localhost:5001/api/auth/refreshToken/YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Forgot Password
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### 5. Reset Password (replace token and email from forgot password email)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "token": "YOUR_RESET_TOKEN_HERE",
  "newPassword": "NewPassword123!"
}

### 6. Verify Email (replace with actual token and email from verification email)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/verify-email?email=test@example.com&token=YOUR_VERIFICATION_TOKEN_HERE

### 7. Resend Verification Email
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/resend-verification
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### Register Admin User
POST http://localhost:5001/api/auth/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "Admin123!",
  "fullName": "Admin User"
}

